---
name: pr
description: Push current branch and create a pull request
user-invocable: true
allowed-tools:
  - Bash(git *)
  - Bash(gh *)
---

Create a pull request from the current branch:

1. Check current branch — refuse if on main.
2. Push to remote with `-u` flag if needed.
3. Run `git log main..HEAD` and `git diff main...HEAD --stat` to understand all changes.
4. Create a PR using `gh pr create` with:
   - Short title (under 70 chars) using conventional commit prefix
   - Body with ## Summary (bullet points) and ## Test plan
5. Report the PR URL.
